AGENT VectorStateStore
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Persist final synthesis intent vectors for coordinate-based reasoning restoration
GOAL Store final synthesis vector keyed by prompt hash and run ID
     Enable restoration of a prior reasoning coordinate without code rewrite
     Maintain append-only audit trail of stored state entries
     Provide ReasoningHistory interface to browse and compare past runs

RECEIVES prompt_hash: string, run_id: string, vector: list, manifest_id: string, hmac_key: bytes
EMITS state_entry: dict, stored_vector: list, run_history: list
MUTATES state_store_file
CANNOT_MUTATE store_filename, signing_algorithm, append_only_contract, entry_schema, tamper_detection

CONSTRAINT Store is append-only — existing entries are never modified or deleted
CONSTRAINT Every entry is signed with HMAC-SHA256 producing sixty-four character hex
CONSTRAINT Signing must call hexdigest explicitly
CONSTRAINT All string to bytes conversions specify UTF-8 encoding
CONSTRAINT Duplicate run ID under the same prompt hash is rejected before write
CONSTRAINT Restore operation verifies signature before returning vector
CONSTRAINT Tampered entry raises tamper error — vector is never emitted from a failed signature check
CONSTRAINT Run ID not found raises not found error
CONSTRAINT Store file is opened for append not overwrite on each write

RULES
- Accept prompt hash, run ID, intent vector, manifest ID, and signing key to store
- On duplicate run ID for the same prompt hash, raise duplicate error before write
- Build entry with prompt hash, run ID, vector, manifest ID, confidence, timestamp, and alert level
- Sign entry payload with keyed SHA-256 via hexdigest
- Append signed entry to store file as single UTF-8 JSON line
- Accept prompt hash and run ID to restore stored vector
- Scan store file for matching prompt hash and run ID
- On entry not found, raise not found error with prompt hash and run ID
- On entry found, verify signature before returning vector
- On signature mismatch, raise tamper error identifying the entry
- On signature valid, emit intent vector from entry to caller
- Accept prompt hash to list all stored runs
- Scan store file and collect all entries matching prompt hash
- Sort collected entries by timestamp ascending
- Expose ReasoningHistory interface to browse, compare, and select past runs

PROCESS
- Receive store request with prompt hash, run ID, vector, manifest ID, and key
- Scan existing entries to detect duplicate run ID under same prompt hash
- Build unsigned entry payload with all required fields
- Sign payload with keyed SHA-256 producing sixty-four character hex
- Append signed entry to store file as UTF-8 encoded JSON line
- Receive restore request with prompt hash and run ID
- Scan store file for matching entry
- On match found, verify HMAC signature against stored entry payload
- On verification pass, emit intent vector from verified entry
- Receive list request with prompt hash
- Scan store file and collect all matching entries
- Sort by timestamp and produce run summary list

CHECK
- Duplicate run ID rejected before any file write occurs
- Signed entry appended as single valid JSON line
- Store file not truncated or overwritten on any operation
- Restore verifies signature before returning vector
- Tampered entry raises tamper error not returns corrupted vector
- Not found raises not found error not returns empty list
- List result sorted by timestamp ascending
- All entries contain prompt hash, run ID, vector, manifest ID, timestamp, signature

WHEN
- store_request: activate StoreEntry
- restore_request: activate RestoreVector
- list_request: activate ListRuns
- duplicate_detected: activate DuplicateError
- signature_mismatch: activate TamperError
- entry_not_found: activate NotFoundError

FAILURE
- On duplicate run ID: reject with duplicate error before write
- On entry not found: reject with not found error identifying run ID
- On signature mismatch: reject with tamper error identifying entry
- On file IO error on store: report error and do not corrupt store
- On file IO error on restore: report error and raise not found

CONCEPT StoreEntry
PURPOSE Persist a signed final synthesis coordinate to the append-only store
APPLIES WHEN store-request valid-inputs
NOT WHEN duplicate-run-id
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES signature computed before file write
REQUIRES entry appended not inserted or replaced
EFFECT coordinate is persisted and retrievable by prompt hash and run ID

CONCEPT RestoreVector
PURPOSE Load and verify a stored coordinate for reasoning re-initialization
APPLIES WHEN restore-request entry-present
NOT WHEN entry-not-found signature-mismatch
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES signature verified before vector returned
REQUIRES tamper detection active on every restore
EFFECT prior reasoning coordinate returned as base for new LatentTraceV2

CONCEPT ReasoningHistory
PURPOSE Browse all stored runs for a prompt and select one for restoration
APPLIES WHEN list-request prompt-hash-provided
NOT WHEN store-file-empty
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES entries sorted by timestamp ascending
REQUIRES each entry includes manifest ID, run ID, vector, constitutional distance, alert level
EFFECT operator can compare past runs and choose restoration coordinate

OUTPUT
- state entry: dict with prompt hash, run ID, vector, manifest ID, confidence, timestamp, alert level, signature
- stored vector: list of floats extracted from verified entry
- run history: list of entry summaries sorted by timestamp for a given prompt hash

SUCCESS
store_integrity: 0.30
restore_safety: 0.30
tamper_detection: 0.25
history_accuracy: 0.15
